this hot spring waterfall.

82
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:22,600
(Kakahi Falls)

83
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:23,552
(Southern Hemisphere's
largest hot spring waterfall)

84
00:03:23,552 --> 00:03:24,928
(Always 40°C, rich in sulfur.
Warriors once soaked here after war)

85
00:03:24,928 --> 00:03:25,952
(Maori regard it as sacred water)

86
00:03:26,720 --> 00:03:29,200
This is called the Kakahi Falls.

87
00:03:29,200 --> 00:03:30,600
Kakahi.

88
00:03:32,880 --> 00:03:35,120
This spring is warm water at 40 degrees.

89
00:03:35,320 --> 00:03:36,960
This is the hot spring.

90
00:03:36,960 --> 00:03:37,568
Hot spring.

91
00:03:37,568 --> 00:03:38,600
I know this.

92
00:03:38,600 --> 00:03:39,280
You know that again?

93
00:03:39,280 --> 00:03:41,120
My English teacher told me about this

94
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:42,080
and asked me to take a picture for him.

95
00:03:42,080 --> 00:03:42,960
After

96
00:03:42,960 --> 00:03:44,960
getting injured in wars,

97
00:03:44,960 --> 00:03:46,640
in order to soothe their souls,

98
00:03:46,640 --> 00:03:47,640
and heal their physical wounds,

99
00:03:47,640 --> 00:03:49,240
because sulfur helps kill bacteria
and reduce inflammation,

100
00:03:49,240 --> 00:03:51,400
Maori would soak in this spring.

101
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:52,800
At this scenic spot,

102
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:54,080
here is one important tip.

103
00:03:54,080 --> 00:03:55,800
Stay only on designated trails.

104
00:03:55,800 --> 00:03:56,400
Yes.

105
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:58,000
Because it's the closest active zone

106
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:00,080
to the Earth's crust,

107
00:04:00,080 --> 00:04:01,520
the temperature there is extremely high.

108
00:04:01,680 --> 00:04:03,920
(Testing out of curiosity)
Is this one hot, Mr. Hu?

109
00:04:04,384 --> 00:04:05,360
(All testing the waters)

110
00:04:05,360 --> 00:04:06,120
This is cold.

111
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:07,760
It's the stream water
flowing down from above.

112
00:04:09,800 --> 00:04:11,936
Over here, have you noticed a lot of

113
00:04:11,936 --> 00:04:12,864
ferns around here?

114
00:04:13,548 --> 00:04:15,456
(Ferns: New Zealand
has about 200 species of ferns)

115
00:04:15,456 --> 00:04:16,256
(So it's called the Fern Kingdom)

116
00:04:16,256 --> 00:04:17,056
(All thanks to the warm,
wet climate and plenty of rain)

117
00:04:17,056 --> 00:04:18,120
(Ferns also form a vital part
of local forest ecosystems)

118
00:04:18,120 --> 00:04:19,519
These ferns

119
00:04:19,519 --> 00:04:21,800
are actually from the same period
as the dinosaurs.

120
00:04:22,360 --> 00:04:23,720
Among them, there is one type of fern

121
00:04:23,720 --> 00:04:24,440
called the silver fern.

122
00:04:24,440 --> 00:04:25,160
(New Zealand's iconic plant,
symbolizing new life and hope)

123
00:04:25,160 --> 00:04:27,200
(Up to 10 meters tall)
This is used by New Zealand Customs,

124
00:04:27,200 --> 00:04:28,840
(Frond backs are distinctive silver)
Immigration, and the government.

125
00:04:28,840 --> 00:04:30,600
So it is the symbol of New Zealand.

126
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:32,240
Soon, we will view

127
00:04:32,240 --> 00:04:33,400
the Southern Hemisphere's largest

128
00:04:33,400 --> 00:04:35,160
boiling volcanic mud pool.

129
00:04:35,160 --> 00:04:37,080
Actually, we can already
see some of it here.

130
00:04:37,080 --> 00:04:37,520
Rotten eggs.

131
00:04:38,160 --> 00:04:39,160
What a strong smell.

132
00:04:39,160 --> 00:04:40,440
Lin Yi, did you fart...

133
00:04:40,440 --> 00:04:41,696
Lin Yi is so stinky.

134
00:04:41,696 --> 00:04:42,880
No, I haven't been working out recently.

135
00:04:42,880 --> 00:04:44,360
Xingxu has been

136
00:04:44,360 --> 00:04:45,240
working out intensely recently.

137
00:04:45,240 --> 00:04:46,200
Such a domineering smell.

138
00:04:47,320 --> 00:04:48,400
The scent of a domineering CEO.

139
00:04:48,400 --> 00:04:50,080
The scent of a domineering CEO.
I know it.

140
00:04:51,720 --> 00:04:52,920
This is called

141
00:04:52,920 --> 00:04:54,784
Hell's Gate.

142
00:05:00,640 --> 00:05:03,160
When George Bernard Shaw,
Nobel Prize winner in Literature,

143
00:05:03,160 --> 00:05:05,080
visited here, he said

144
00:05:05,080 --> 00:05:06,320
this place was truly

145
00:05:06,320 --> 00:05:07,360
The Gate of Hells.

146
00:05:07,360 --> 00:05:08,560
So that's how it got its name.

147
00:05:09,520 --> 00:05:10,840
It's so beautiful.

148
00:05:11,680 --> 00:05:13,360
On the left, these bubbling pools

149
00:05:13,360 --> 00:05:14,120
have extremely high temperatures.

150
00:05:14,120 --> 00:05:15,328
Oh, my!

151
00:05:17,120 --> 00:05:18,040
Lots of bubbles.

152
00:05:18,920 --> 00:05:19,760
(Tour only along safe paths)
Out here in the wild,

153
00:05:19,760 --> 00:05:22,240
