193
00:06:35,800 --> 00:06:36,864
We're about to go fishing.

194
00:06:40,680 --> 00:06:42,200
(Cooking Pool)
We drop food into the pool to cook,

195
00:06:42,200 --> 00:06:43,640
and then pull it out later.

196
00:06:43,640 --> 00:06:45,200
It's actually like a hot pot.

197
00:06:45,200 --> 00:06:46,528
It's a bit similar to a hot pot.

198
00:06:46,560 --> 00:06:47,552
(The geothermal DIY hot pot is here)
Shrimp.

199
00:06:47,640 --> 00:06:48,440
Corn.

200
00:06:48,440 --> 00:06:49,680
I love eating this.

201
00:06:50,960 --> 00:06:52,040
It's very simple.

202
00:06:52,040 --> 00:06:53,920
First get a small cloth bag.

203
00:06:54,560 --> 00:06:57,120
Choose some food you like.

204
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:58,880
For example, sweet potatoes.

205
00:06:59,240 --> 00:07:00,960
These are mussels. Mussel.

206
00:07:01,200 --> 00:07:02,360
Then just tie a tight knot.

207
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:02,800
Okay.

208
00:07:02,800 --> 00:07:04,880
Place the bag into the pool,

209
00:07:04,880 --> 00:07:06,304
and weigh it down with a rock.

210
00:07:06,752 --> 00:07:07,600
Oh, my.

211
00:07:07,600 --> 00:07:09,960
Such a fantastic experience.

212
00:07:09,960 --> 00:07:10,800
This is quite interesting.

213
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:13,440
(Heart says go, so go)
I want to eat eggs. I'm a bit hungry.

214
00:07:13,440 --> 00:07:14,960
Let's get a hot sticky corn.

215
00:07:15,992 --> 00:07:17,280
(High-quality protein)

216
00:07:17,280 --> 00:07:18,880
(From Hell's Gate to the king of the curb)
Will the egg break

217
00:07:18,880 --> 00:07:19,920
if we weigh it down with a rock?

218
00:07:21,960 --> 00:07:22,560
It's good.

219
00:07:22,560 --> 00:07:23,920
Why is your bag so big?

220
00:07:24,960 --> 00:07:26,360
I can even put a whole leg in there.

221
00:07:28,040 --> 00:07:29,200
Tie it up here?

222
00:07:29,200 --> 00:07:30,440
(Ingredients are picked)
Yes, tie a tight knot.

223
00:07:30,440 --> 00:07:31,760
Got it.

224
00:07:31,760 --> 00:07:33,280
If you don't tie a tight knot,
the bag will fall off.

225
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:38,280
Gong Jun.

226
00:07:38,280 --> 00:07:38,720
What?

227
00:07:39,200 --> 00:07:39,800
What happened?

228
00:07:40,416 --> 00:07:41,120
(Chen Xingxu)

229
00:07:41,120 --> 00:07:42,000
(Fluffy)
Bro, sorry.

230
00:07:43,680 --> 00:07:44,600
You must weigh it down with a rock.

231
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:45,960
Without a stone weighing it down,

232
00:07:45,960 --> 00:07:46,840
the buoyancy will keep it floating.

233
00:07:47,920 --> 00:07:49,520
Just slowly lower it in.

234
00:07:49,520 --> 00:07:50,240
I just put one in.

235
00:07:54,560 --> 00:07:55,320
It's so heavy.

236
00:07:55,320 --> 00:07:55,960
It's so heavy.

237
00:07:57,040 --> 00:07:57,640
Let's swing it.

238
00:07:58,480 --> 00:08:00,720
One, two...

239
00:08:00,720 --> 00:08:01,600
When I say "three", throw it.

240
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:03,440
Three.

241
00:08:03,808 --> 00:08:05,056
Oh, my God!

242
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:07,200
This is better.

243
00:08:07,200 --> 00:08:08,560
Ours is so heavy.

244
00:08:08,560 --> 00:08:10,080
That's right.

245
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:13,840
This is way too interesting.

246
00:08:13,840 --> 00:08:14,600
Very interesting.

247
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:16,240
Really a great experience.

248
00:08:16,240 --> 00:08:17,320
Can we eat it now?

249
00:08:17,320 --> 00:08:18,120
No.

250
00:08:18,120 --> 00:08:19,520
Is it pre-made food?

251
00:08:19,520 --> 00:08:20,840
Ready straight away?

252
00:08:23,600 --> 00:08:24,840
Then how will I know if my bag

253
00:08:24,840 --> 00:08:25,640
