256
00:08:28,360 --> 00:08:29,000
Ye.

257
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:31,280
People down below will help us.

258
00:08:31,280 --> 00:08:31,880
Okay.

259
00:08:31,880 --> 00:08:33,360
(Almost believe it)
If your bag goes down, they'll replace it for you.

260
00:08:33,360 --> 00:08:34,320
Then you pull it back up.

261
00:08:34,320 --> 00:08:34,760
Okay.

262
00:08:34,760 --> 00:08:36,039
Must be a "well-done" friend.
[*A pun on "acquaintance" in Chinese]

263
00:08:36,039 --> 00:08:36,544
(A "well-done" friend)
Yes.

264
00:08:37,520 --> 00:08:38,360
Pretty well-done.

265
00:08:38,360 --> 00:08:39,240
I don't have many "well-done" friends.

266
00:08:41,039 --> 00:08:42,480
Let's continue walking forward.

267
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:43,960
Just leave it there to cook.

268
00:08:43,960 --> 00:08:44,480
Okay.

269
00:08:45,024 --> 00:08:47,040
(Cooking in progress)

270
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:48,640
We're at the Steam Cliffs.

271
00:08:48,640 --> 00:08:49,360
(Steam Cliffs: One of Hell's Gate's
most jaw-dropping sights,)

272
00:08:49,360 --> 00:08:50,840
(and the hottest spot in the whole reserve)
Steam Cliffs.

273
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:52,080
(Thanks to the minerals in the water,)

274
00:08:52,080 --> 00:08:53,320
(the main spring
can hit a blistering 110 to 120°C)

275
00:08:53,320 --> 00:08:54,520
It's bubbling and gurgling.

276
00:08:59,520 --> 00:09:00,520
A natural wonder.

277
00:09:00,520 --> 00:09:01,120
It's so magical.

278
00:09:02,080 --> 00:09:05,344
(Sun Honglei)

